      <subfield code="a">Religion and psychotherapy in modern Japan : a four-phaseview -- Psychiatry and religion in modern Japan : traditional temple and shrine therapies -- The birth of Japanese mind cure methods -- The mind and healing in Morita therapy -- The dawning of Japanese psychoanalysis : Kosawa Heisaku's therapy and faith -- Doi Takeo and the development of the 'Amae' theory -- From salvation to healing : Yoshimoto Naikan therapy and its religious origins -- Naikan and mourning : a Catholic attempt at Naikan meditation -- Kawai Hayao's transnational identity and Japanese spirit -- The contemporary view of reincarnation in Japan : narratives of the reincarnating self -- A society accepting of spirit possession : mental health and shamanism in Okinawa -- Chaplaincy work in disaster areas.</subfield>
